               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p>In the Captaincy of São Vicente, Jesuit missionary José de Anchieta described Tibiriçá as someone with “such maturity that he did not seem like a man of Brazil” (<htcite0>). This perspective reinforces the notion of superiority, which likely influenced conflicts such as the massacre of the so-called “Confederation of the Tamoios” (<htcite1>).</p><p>Indigenous thinker Ailton Krenak broadens this critical view of colonization; for that reason, we recommend readers study his works (<htcite2>).</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 0,
                     "uuid": "ef2da4a7-021f-48d6-b8b5-5e343ceffbba",
                     "text": "Anchieta, José de, Santo",
                     "page": "pp. 187",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1933",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "edf91bed-62b7-4dcd-bd1a-23e873bc372c",
                     "text": "Perrone-Moisés, Beatriz, and Sztutman, Renato",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2010",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "5c6a2e44-9bbe-410f-a505-d3994389d750",
                     "text": "Krenak, Ailton",
                     "page": "pp. 7-16",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2019",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
