      {
         "id": "SECTION_indigenousvision",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<h3>The Indigenous Perspective</h3><p>Due to the destruction of texts and the absence of writing among some Indigenous peoples, it is difficult to categorically affirm that notions of superiority never existed among them. What is known is that wars occurred in Mesoamerica—though very different from those in Eurasia (<htcite0>).</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "c6d9c6f6-2e8b-4e53-8e4a-f8f29fbbeec9",
                     "text": "Chase, Arlen F., Chase, Diane Z.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "1998",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "1998",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_science",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Would there be any view of equality?</h3>In the <i>Popol-Vuh</i>, the Maya sacred text, there is a passage that links humans and monkeys as part of the same “creation project,” suggesting a certain sense of equality (<htcite0>; <htcite1> ; <htcite2>): <ul class=\"citation\"><li><i>\"It is said that their descendants are the monkeys now living in the forests. These monkeys are all that remain of them because their flesh was made only of wood by the Creator and the Maker. And so, the monkey resembles humans, serving as an example of a generation of people who were created and shaped, but were merely figures made of wood.\"</i></li></ul></p><p>Centuries later, Charles Darwin would record, through scientific observation, the equality of all <i>\"Homo sapiens\"</i> via a common ancestor (<htcite3>).</p><p>Although the Maya and Darwinian conclusions may appear similar, they are in fact based on very different premises.</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "bb8148ed-01cf-47fc-b941-5af304945e66",
                     "text": "Vela, Enrique",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2007",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 2,
                     "uuid": "8fcee36c-411a-4fc8-8217-b9a07a34d3da",
                     "text": "Popol Vuh",
                     "page": "pp. 39",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 2,
                     "uuid": "74bdb72d-1770-4694-8f8e-71e680f1d49c",
                     "text": "Popol Vuh, , Ch. 3",
                     "page": "pp. 8",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "e1339d6e-ab15-42c8-a75b-7a42fa47fffd",
                     "text": "Darwin, Charles, 19--, Vol. I",
                     "page": "pp. 57",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2023",
                        "month": "10",
                        "day": "29"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2007",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2021",
                     "month": "-1",
